6
00:00:56,200 --> 00:01:03,200
Living in a contemporary global capitalistic world, one that has siphoned out any radical economic dissent,

7
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:08,200
the question looms, are we able to escape capitalism? Is there anything past it?

8
00:01:08,200 --> 00:01:15,200
Is any such endeavor even possible? To an arguable majority, they understand the looming issues with capitalism,

9
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:20,200
even if it's something painful to admit. But this supposedly post-ideological world,

10
00:01:20,200 --> 00:01:25,200
a world with the end of the Soviet Union, of an actual communist Chinese government,

11
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:31,200
is there any coherent vision past global capitalism? This is a central ethos of this book.

12
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:38,200
Can we escape capitalism? What is capitalism? And what is this capitalist realism that Mark Fisher talks about?

13
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:43,200
It should be noted before the body of the video, I have been told numerous times to read this book in its whole,

14
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:49,200
